"Abstract The software industry constitutes a significant and growing sector of the Scottish economy. In common with many aspects of computerisation, the application of traditional legal rules to these new products is not without difficulty. Although a good deal has been written on the topic of software liability, less is known of views and experiences of those involved in the industry. An EC funded research project SCOPE (Software Certification in Europe Programme) is seeking to facilitate the development of product standards and promote the introduction of a system of software certification to allow customers to acquire software with an enhanced degree of confidence that it will be suitable for their needs. As part of this project, a survey was conducted among Scottish software companies seeking their views and opinions on a variety of legal topics. The present article seeks to distill and present the main results of the survey."
